DATA INTEGRATION

Data integration in this project involves the seamless transmission and processing of input and output signals across various hardware and software modules. When a gesture is detected by the PAJ7620 sensor, its signal is transmitted to the Arduino Uno for processing. If the gesture matches a predefined access gesture, the Arduino checks the encrypted access code using RC4 decryption. Upon successful authentication, the system triggers the door lock mechanism and updates the LCD display. In the case of failed access or unauthorized gestures, an alert is generated, and the Resend API is called via serial communication (through a connected module or PC) to dispatch a security notification via email. This integrated flow ensures secure, real-time decision-making, smooth coordination among modules, and effective user feedback and alerting.
         

